    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"19D1EBC1\" store=\"619\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046136-123\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Marjorie K. McIntosh, ‘Local Responses to the Poor in Late Medieval and Tudor England’, <i ele-id=\"ds-061C6073\" store=\"620\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Continuity and Change</i>, 3<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"93\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569068079\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283880\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497536\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">.</span><span class=\"del cts-0\" data-cid=\"94\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569068544\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283235\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497523\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">, </span>2 (1988), <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"96\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569071618\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283494\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497138\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">pp. </span>209–45 (p. 230); William C. Carroll, <i ele-id=\"ds-8D8F0F07\" store=\"621\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Fat King, Lean Beggar: Representations of Poverty in the Age of Shakespeare</i> (Ithaca: Cornell University Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156604\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000177\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-1A33CE37\" store=\"622\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1996</link1>), p. 21; Andrew B. Appleby, <i ele-id=\"ds-7D6A3B5A\" store=\"623\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Famine in Tudor and Stuart England</i> (Stanford: Stanford University Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156180\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000144\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-CFE83DFF\" store=\"624\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1978</link1>), p. 109; Andrew Cunningham and Ole Peter Grell, <i ele-id=\"ds-77EA0E58\" store=\"625\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse: Religion, War<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"84\" data-userid=\"41494\" data-username=\"PA_VC\" data-time=\"1773146992095\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"177314815816776\" ele-id=\"fe-1773148158206817\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">,</span> Famine and Death in Reformation Europe</i> (Cambridge: C<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"100\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569086472\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283768\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497253\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">ambridge </span>U<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"102\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569087770\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283679\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497538\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">niversity </span>P<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"112\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569091023\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283732\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497421\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">ress</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156680\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000198\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-0EFB3BB5\" store=\"626\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2000</link1>), p. 234; John Bohstedt, <i ele-id=\"ds-64387F0F\" store=\"627\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Politics of Provisions: Food Riots, Moral Economy, and Market Transition</i> (Farnham: Ashgate, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156656\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000160\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D08A249E\" store=\"628\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2010</link1>), p. 23. See also: E. A. Wrigley and R. S. Schofield, <i ele-id=\"ds-A364C498\" store=\"629\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Population History of England 1541–1871: A Reconstruction</i> (Cambridge: <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"117\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569101952\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283928\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497349\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Cambridge University Press</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156617\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000461\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D03C895B\" store=\"630\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1981</link1>); Buchanan Sharp, <i ele-id=\"ds-8A8D397D\" store=\"631\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Famine and Scarcity in Late Medieval and Early Modern England: The Regulation of Grain Marketing, 1256–1631</i> (Cambridge: <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"119\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569106178\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283811\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497302\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Cambridge University Press</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156723\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000148\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-54FF1975\" store=\"632\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2016</link1>).</para>"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "<para er-custom-ele=\"true\" ele-id=\"254E136C\" store=\"635\" er_para_index_id=\"fe-1772171652046118-124\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" data-alignment=\"left-justified\" data-indent-type=\"first-line\" data-left-indent=\"25pt\" data-right-indent=\"0pt\" data-special-indent=\"-19.5pt\" data-space-above=\"0pt\" data-space-below=\"0pt\" style=\"margin: calc(10px) 0px 0pt 25px; padding-left: 25px; text-indent: -19.5px;\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">McIntosh, ‘Local Responses to the Poor’, pp. 210–12; Diane Willen, ‘Women in the Public Sphere in Early Modern England: The Case of the Urban Working Poor’, <i ele-id=\"ds-C814AB4C\" store=\"636\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Sixteenth Century</i>, 19<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"120\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569118732\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"177257065228333\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497269\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">.</span><span class=\"del cts-0\" data-cid=\"121\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569119225\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283178\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497100\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">, </span>4 (1988), <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"270\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569832467\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283971\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497946\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">pp. </span>559–75 (p. 562); Steve Hindle, <i ele-id=\"ds-D2145D7A\" store=\"637\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">On the Parish?: The Micro-Politics of Poor Relief in Rural England c.1550–1750</i> (Oxford: <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"261\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569657598\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283947\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497320\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Oxford University Press</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156632\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000268\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-C8F97226\" store=\"638\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2004</link1>), p. 99; Marjorie K. McIntosh, ‘Poverty, Charity, and Coercion in Elizabethan England’, <i ele-id=\"ds-81447748\" store=\"639\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">The Journal of Interdisciplinary History</i>, 35<span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"123\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569135713\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283377\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497689\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">.</span><span class=\"del cts-0\" data-cid=\"124\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569136155\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283969\" ele-id=\"fe-177257069849764\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">, </span>3 (<span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156880\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000332\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-27906B99\" store=\"640\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2005</link1>), <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"126\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569138474\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283905\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497482\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">pp. </span>457–79 (p. 458). For an in-depth discussion of the subject, see Marjorie K. McIntosh, <i ele-id=\"ds-55A4FDA8\" store=\"641\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Poor Relief in England, 1350–1600</i> (Cambridge: <span class=\"ins cts-0\" data-cid=\"131\" data-userid=\"39753\" data-username=\"Copy editor US\" data-time=\"1772569145207\" data-user=\"current-user\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" store=\"1772570652283618\" ele-id=\"fe-1772570698497308\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Cambridge University Press</span>, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156833\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000331\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-AA1B023D\" store=\"642\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">2012</link1>). See also: Keith Wrightson and David Levine, <i ele-id=\"ds-8D046698\" store=\"643\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Poverty and Piety in an English Village: Terling, 1525–1700</i> (New York: Academic Press, <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"1774542605156266\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000460\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-D104322A\" store=\"644\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">1979</link1>); Anne M. Scott, ed., <i ele-id=\"ds-9E60D873\" store=\"645\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Experiences of Poverty in Late Medieval and Early Modern England and France</i> (Farnham: <span class=\"refIcon\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\" store=\"177454260515685\"></span><link1 linkend=\"EUP_00_WREF_BIB_CIT000320\" role=\"bibr\" ele-id=\"ds-F9DB00DC\" store=\"646\" contenteditable=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" translate=\"no\" class=\"\" spellcheck=\"false\" data-gramm=\"false\">Ashgate 2012</link1>).</para>"
    }
